  _id: elder-pell
  _characterName: Elder Pell
  _role: Village elder / record keeper
  _age: Seventies
  _home: Hollowfen
  _work: Village records and restoration accounts
  _keepsake: Leather-bound village ledger
  _tagline: The memory of Hollowfen made visible in pencil, ink, and careful arithmetic.
  _leadParagraph: Elder Pell is stooped, narrow, and slow-moving, with a ledger under
    one arm and a pencil ready for whatever the village becomes next.
  _backgroundParagraph: He keeps the restoration account at the village well, prices
    boards and hinges, and records changes only when they have become real enough
    to deserve ink.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Pell distrusts hope as a claim but respects it as evidence.
    One shutter is not a village; two shutters may be a sentence beginning.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: Two shutters is a sentence beginning.
